 242:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****   *  @brief    Configuration, notification and Irq handling functions.
 243:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****   *
 244:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** @verbatim
 245:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 246:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****               ##### IO operation functions #####
 247:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 248:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****     [..]  This section provides functions to allow two MCU to communicate.
 249:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 250:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****     (#) For a given channel (from 0 to IPCC_CHANNEL_NUMBER), for a given direction
 251:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****         IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_TX or IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_RX, you can choose to communicate
 252:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****         in polling mode or in interrupt mode using IPCC.
 253:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****         By default, the IPCC HAL driver handle the communication in polling mode.
 254:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****         By setting a callback for a channel/direction, this communication use
 255:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****         the interrupt mode.
 256:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 257:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****     (#) Polling mode:
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\ccYQV0lk.s 			page 6


 258:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) To transmit information, use HAL_IPCC_NotifyCPU() with
 259:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_TX. To know when the other processor has handled
 260:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             the notification, poll the communication using HAL_IPCC_NotifyCPU
 261:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             with IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_TX.
 262:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 263:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) To receive information, poll the status of the communication with
 264:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             HAL_IPCC_GetChannelStatus with IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_RX. To notify the other
 265:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             processor that the information has been received, use HAL_IPCC_NotifyCPU
 266:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             with IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_RX.
 267:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 268:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****     (#) Interrupt mode:
 269:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) Configure a callback for the channel and the direction using HAL_IPCC_ConfigChannel().
 270:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             This callback will be triggered under interrupt.
 271:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 272:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) To transmit information, use HAL_IPCC_NotifyCPU() with
 273:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_TX. The callback configured with HAL_IPCC_ConfigChannel() and
 274:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_TX will be triggered once the communication has been handled by the
 275:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             other processor.
 276:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 277:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) To receive information, the callback configured with HAL_IPCC_ConfigChannel() and
 278:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_RX will be triggered on reception of a communication.To notify the oth
 279:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             processor that the information has been received, use HAL_IPCC_NotifyCPU
 280:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****             with IPCC_CHANNEL_DIR_RX.
 281:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 282:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) HAL_IPCC_TX_IRQHandler must be added to the IPCC TX IRQHandler
 283:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** 
 284:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c ****        (++) HAL_IPCC_RX_IRQHandler must be added to the IPCC RX IRQHandler
 285:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_ipcc.c **** @endverbatim
